Excel Macros
Macros in Excel: Sequences of instructions that automate repetitive tasks.
Recording a Macro: Actions can be recorded to capture a series of steps in Excel.
Running a Macro: Once recorded, macros can be executed to repeat the captured actions.
Macros Security: Security settings for enabling or disabling macros in Excel.
VBA (Visual Basic for Applications)
VBA: A programming language integrated into Microsoft Office applications.
Capabilities: Allows users to write custom code to automate tasks, create user-defined functions, and control Excel.
VBA Concepts
VBA Editor: The integrated development environment (IDE) where you write and edit VBA code.
Modules: Containers for VBA code within a workbook.
Procedures: Subroutines (Sub) and functions (Function) that perform specific tasks.
Macro vs. VBA
Macro: A piece of code.
Language: Macros are written in a programming language called VBA.
Application: VBA is used in Excel, Word, PowerPoint, and other Office applications.
Editor: VBA includes an editor within Excel and Word for writing and managing macros.